{"id":14881868,"mediaExerciseId":"fea866f5-e7e8-40b2-bb0f-6ac63763ed05","exerciseName":"11","chapterName":"24","chapterTitle":"Options and Corporate Finance","groupId":612498,"groupTitle":"Critical Thinking Questions","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":823,"solutions":[{"id":5999956,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this problem, we must determine the option to abandon and explain why we underestimate NPV if we ignore this option.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"### Define the option to abandon.\n\nThe option to abandon is to abandon a project with a negative or zero Net Present Value (NPV). The company decided to give up the project entirely because it could not cover its expenses.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":66,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/09/aafa7ca8b6a920e071c9e39898d52bfe/aebf3e17aed17c04adb453b4f462f1f5/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":34,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/09/aafa7ca8b6a920e071c9e39898d52bfe/aebf3e17aed17c04adb453b4f462f1f5/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"### Explain why we underestimate NPV if we ignore this option.\n\nIf this option is ignored, the NPV is underestimated because, in this option, we can minimize losses, which has a positive effect on the NPV. If a project cannot cover its expenses, it is better to abandon it. In the hope that the project can be redesigned, NPV is ignored or underestimated.\n","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3}],"rating":5,"solutionUuid":"810f181b-c518-47a8-9190-cbf152415dc8","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps"